UNITHY

The world is adapting to home sharing apps but major cities are applying taxes to the hosts. With UNITHY we want to reduce those high fees and verify rentals to our community so that the travelers can save money and the host can earn more money while paying their taxes.

See the video

Home sharing apps is a 51-billion-dollar market expanding each year, and their main revenue is the high fees. UNITHY features Dapp (decentralized application) where our community can access the platform via a web page or by the simple use of their smart phone. You’ll have access to a wide selection of luxuries houses and exotic places at a reasonable price with verified users and houses. No more headaches of doubting if your host or rental is legal, with our smart contracts every verify user will be stored in the Ethereum blockchain with our own encrypted software.

Problems in Home Sharing Apps…

Customer Service

Takes too long with refund, denies refund unfairly or for no reason. Customer Service refused to help with a problem that would typically be their responsibility

Fake listings or reviews (SCAM)

Reviews of listing/host are falsified in any way (e.g. duplicated good reviews to look better, deleted or denied bad reviews, Home sharing apps removes a review for no reason)

$50 billion Market only with High FEES

Home Sharing Apps is a 50 billion dolar market, and their main revenue is HIGH FEES.

Is the rental legal ?

The process of KYC (know your costumer) is unknown by the home sharing apps. Anyone with an email and a phone number can create a profile and rent any place.
 
 

UNITHY, Innovating Home Sharing with blockchain

UNITHY Judge System

UNITHY stake holder feature will integrate masternodes for its smart contracts and adopts the masternode governing system for its Congress Network.

Smart Contracts

Smart contracts help you exchange money, property, shares, or anything of value in a transparent, conflict-free way while avoiding the services of a middleman.

Low-Fee

UNITHY’s aims to provide the first home sharing app with low fees so that our users can earn the most with their rentals. Travelers will be able to travel more by saving money with UNITHY.

KYC Process

UNITHY will enforce bank-level KYC (Know Your Customer) processes to comply with AML (Anti Money Laundering) laws. The process usually be completed within 24 hours of customer submission.

Stake Holders

UNITHY stake holder feature will integrate masternodes for its smart contracts and adopts the masternode governing system for its Congress Network. Taking their cue from Dash’s masternode voting mechanism, UNITHY developers created Congress Network to improve governance and decision making within the network. Under this system, masternode operators are given voting privileges to decide on blockchain revenue allocation, code and policy modifications. Not forgetting that each UNITHY masternode holder will receive monthly rewards.

The Congress Network will be limited to 2.000 users

To become an UNITHY stake holder you will need to have 20.000 UNY. The stake holder user will send the UNY to a smart contract or Congress Network that will held the tokens for 1 month. The reward system is directly proportional to the amount of users in the Congress Network, the more stake holders the reward will be divided by more users. Each stake holder will receive 2000 UNY a month for becoming part of the Congress Network. After each month the stake holders will receive the 20.000 UNY back plus the 2.000 UNY where they can decide to become part of the Congress Network again or not..
